I had a friend over sunday so I couldn't get online.

* She gave a surprised snarl when Prowl suddenly caught hold of her and they 
were both lifted into the air. She not only hated heights but she was ready 
to bound away from Menasor before he would have crushed her and now her 
muscles ached a little from not leaping like they thought they were supposed 
to.
Looking up at Prowl she hissed at him, then heaving a sigh and looking down, 
seeing the land fly away from under her feet...way...way down below her.
The battle was going pretty well now, the alliance, or most of it, had gone 
and now there was only half that many bots to deal with.
She sighed again and kicked a little, not liking it when her feet couldn't 
be touching something. But she had to admit, it was a neat side effect that 
when she transformed into her SBM that Prowl did too.
It made her feel not so alone. Being the only alien on the planet before and 
all.
But in this case, Prowl was acking in instinkt and not his brain and she 
might have to teach him how to master this mode, just like he would have to 
teach her how to fly in robot mode.*
